{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891459937,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b611de2001gobhPbJQUUZht2","messageID":"msg_d7b610c5b001HOnrDxkHkRdKfG","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-021/spec.yaml"},"error":"File not found: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-021/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775891459928,"end":1775891459936}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891459945,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b612306001EUjNYvDcoq4URZ","messageID":"msg_d7b610c5b001HOnrDxkHkRdKfG","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: This document describes the delta specification for implementing the `publish` command in the AgentCube CLI.\n5: \n6: ## Current State\n7: - The CLI framework exists with command structure\n8: - The `pack` command (AR-020) creates distributable archives\n9: - No publish functionality exists yet\n10: \n11: ## Target State\n12: A fully functional `publish` command that:\n13: - Uploads packaged agents to the AgentCube registry\n14: - Handles authentication securely\n15: - Provides upload progress feedback\n16: - Validates packages before publishing\n17: \n18: ## Delta Analysis\n19: \n20: ### New Components\n21: 1. **Publish Command Module** (`cmd/cli/publish.py`)\n22:    - CLI interface for publish command\n23:    - Argument parsing and validation\n24:    - Integration with upload logic\n25: \n26: 2. **Registry Client** (`cmd/cli/internal/registry.py`)\n27:    - HTTP client for registry API\n28:    - Authentication handling\n29:    - Upload request construction\n30: \n31: 3. **Authentication Module** (`cmd/cli/internal/auth.py`)\n32:    - API key/token management\n33:    - Credential storage and retrieval\n34: \n35: ### Modified Components\n36: - `cmd/cli/main.py` - Add publish subcommand\n37: \n38: ### Dependencies\n39: - Requires AR-020 (pack command) for package creation\n40: - Uses existing CLI framework\n41: \n42: ## Interface Specification\n43: \n44: ### Command Signature\n45: ```bash\n46: agentcube publish [OPTIONS] <package-file>\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Options\n50: - `--registry, -r`: Target registry URL (default: https://registry.agentcube.io)\n51: - `--api-key, -k`: API key for authentication\n52: - `--dry-run`: Validate without uploading\n53: - `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n54: \n55: ### Exit Codes\n56: - `0`: Success\n57: - `1`: General error\n58: - `2`: Authentication failed\n59: - `3`: Package validation failed\n60: - `4`: Upload failed\n61: \n62: ## Implementation Notes\n63: - Follow existing CLI patterns from other commands\n64: - Use streaming upload for large packages\n65: - Implement exponential backoff for retries\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the `publish` command in the AgentCube CLI.\n\n## Current State\n- The CLI framework exists with command structure\n- The `pack` command (AR-020) creates distributable archives\n- No publish functionality exists yet\n\n## Target State\nA fully functional `publish` command that:\n- Uploads packaged agents to the AgentCube registry\n- Handles authentication securely\n- Provides upload progress feedback\n- Validates packages before publishing\n\n## Delta Analysis\n\n### New Components","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775891459931,"end":1775891459943}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891459947,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6128e4001R626NLYFt56tFF","messageID":"msg_d7b610c5b001HOnrDxkHkRdKfG","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ### Component Diagram\n6: ```\n7: ┌─────────────────┐\n8: │  CLI Interface  │\n9: │  (publish.py)   │\n10: └────────┬────────┘\n11:          │\n12: ┌────────▼────────┐\n13: │  Auth Manager   │\n14: │   (auth.py)     │\n15: └────────┬────────┘\n16:          │\n17: ┌────────▼────────┐\n18: │ Registry Client │\n19: │ (registry.py)   │\n20: └────────┬────────┘\n21:          │ HTTP\n22:     ┌────▼────┐\n23:     │ Registry │\n24:     │  Server  │\n25:     └─────────┘\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ## Key Design Decisions\n29: \n30: ### Authentication\n31: - API keys stored in `~/.agentcube/credentials`\n32: - Support for environment variable `AGENTCUBE_API_KEY`\n33: - Token refresh mechanism for session-based auth\n34: \n35: ### Upload Strategy\n36: - Streaming upload to handle large packages\n37: - Chunked transfer for resumable uploads\n38: - Progress callback for CLI feedback\n39: \n40: ### Error Handling\n41: - Structured error responses from registry\n42: - Retry logic for transient failures\n43: - Clear error messages for users\n44: \n45: ## Data Flow\n46: 1. Parse command arguments\n47: 2. Load authentication credentials\n48: 3. Validate package file\n49: 4. Initialize upload request\n50: 5. Stream package data\n51: 6. Handle response\n52: 7. Report result\n\n(End of file - total 52 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  CLI Interface  │\n│  (publish.py)   │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│  Auth Manager   │\n│   (auth.py)     │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│ Registry Client │\n│ (registry.py)   │\n└────────┬────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775891459933,"end":1775891459945}}}}
