{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891625468,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b61b649001yPosZiyOmhPEnw","messageID":"msg_d7b614c31001nsVBe1DJLU9Tdz","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the `invoke` and `status` commands in the AgentCube CLI.\n\n## Current State\n- The CLI framework exists with command structure\n- Basic commands like `init`, `build`, `pack`, `publish` are available\n- No execution management commands exist yet\n- Backend API for execution management exists (assumed)\n\n## Target State\nFully functional `invoke` and `status` commands that:\n- Allow users to trigger agent executions with custom inputs\n- Enable monitoring of execution status\n- Provide clear output formatting\n- Support both synchronous and asynchronous workflows\n\n## Delta Analysis\n\n### New Components\n\n1. **Invoke Command Module** (`cmd/cli/invoke.py`)\n   - CLI interface for invoke command\n   - Input parameter parsing (JSON file, key-value pairs)\n   - Execution request construction\n   - Immediate response handling with execution ID\n\n2. **Status Command Module** (`cmd/cli/status.py`)\n   - CLI interface for status command\n   - Execution ID validation\n   - Status polling logic\n   - Result display formatting\n\n3. **Execution Client** (`cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`)\n   - HTTP client for execution API\n   - Request/response handling\n   - Error code mapping\n\n4. **Output Formatter** (`cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`)\n   - JSON output formatting\n   - Table output formatting\n   - Color coding for status states\n\n### Modified Components\n- `cmd/cli/main.py` - Add invoke and status subcommands\n\n### Dependencies\n- Requires existing CLI framework\n- Requires backend execution API availability\n- May leverage existing auth module from AR-022\n\n## Interface Specification\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n#### Command Signature\n```bash\nagentcube invoke [OPTIONS] <agent-name-or-id>\n```\n\n#### Options\n- `--input, -i`: Input parameters as JSON string or file path\n- `--input-file, -f`: Path to JSON file containing inputs\n- `--async`: Return immediately with execution ID (default: true)\n- `--sync, -s`: Wait for execution to complete\n- `--timeout`: Timeout for sync mode in seconds (default: 300)\n- `--output, -o`: Output format (json, table, yaml)\n- `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n\n#### Exit Codes\n- `0`: Success (execution completed or submitted)\n- `1`: General error\n- `2`: Agent not found\n- `3`: Invalid input parameters\n- `4`: Execution submission failed\n- `5`: Sync execution timeout\n\n### Status Command\n\n#### Command Signature\n```bash\nagentcube status [OPTIONS] <execution-id>\n```\n\n#### Options\n- `--watch, -w`: Continuously poll for status updates\n- `--interval`: Polling interval in seconds (default: 5)\n- `--output, -o`: Output format (json, table, yaml)\n- `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n\n#### Exit Codes\n- `0`: Execution completed successfully\n- `1`: General error\n- `2`: Execution not found\n- `3`: Execution failed\n- `4`: Execution still running (when not in watch mode)\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Follow existing CLI patterns from other commands\n- Use shared HTTP client for API communication\n- Support both sync and async invocation modes\n- Implement proper polling backoff for status command\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775891625442,"end":1775891625467}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891625470,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b621b61001BYKqRWpIlQfWwK","messageID":"msg_d7b614c31001nsVBe1DJLU9Tdz","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│  CLI Interface  │\n│  (invoke.py)    │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│  CLI Interface  │\n│  (status.py)    │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│Execution Client │\n│(execution.py)   │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│ Output Formatter│\n│ (formatter.py)  │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │ HTTP\n    ┌────▼────┐\n    │Backend  │\n    │   API   │\n    └─────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n### Input Handling\n- Support multiple input formats: JSON string, key-value pairs, JSON file\n- Validate inputs against agent schema before submission\n- Merge multiple input sources (file + CLI args)\n\n### Execution Modes\n- **Async mode (default)**: Submit and return execution ID immediately\n- **Sync mode**: Poll until completion or timeout\n\n### Status Polling\n- Configurable polling interval\n- Exponential backoff for long-running executions\n- Exit immediately when execution completes or fails\n\n### Output Formatting\n- JSON: Machine-readable, complete response data\n- Table: Human-readable, key status fields\n- Support for color-coded status indicators\n\n### Error Handling\n- Clear error messages for common failure scenarios\n- Propagate backend error codes appropriately\n- Graceful handling of network issues\n\n## Data Flow\n\n### Invoke Command\n1. Parse command arguments\n2. Load and validate input parameters\n3. Construct execution request payload\n4. Submit to backend API\n5. Handle response:\n   - Async: Display execution ID\n   - Sync: Poll status until completion\n6. Format and display results\n\n### Status Command\n1. Parse command arguments\n2. Validate execution ID format\n3. Query backend for status\n4. Format and display current state\n5. If watch mode: repeat until terminal state\n\n## API Integration\n\n### Endpoints\n- `POST /api/v1/executions` - Submit new execution\n- `GET /api/v1/executions/{id}` - Query execution status\n- `GET /api/v1/executions/{id}/result` - Fetch execution results\n\n### Response Handling\n- 2xx: Success, parse response body\n- 4xx: Client error, display helpful message\n- 5xx: Server error, suggest retry\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775891625445,"end":1775891625469}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891625472,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b626bce0012mJU3toTLJrN1Q","messageID":"msg_d7b614c31001nsVBe1DJLU9Tdz","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md","content":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation\n\n### Task 1.1: Execution Client Module\n**Objective**: Create the HTTP client for execution API communication\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n2. Implement `ExecutionClient` class\n3. Add methods for:\n   - `submit_execution(agent_id, inputs, options)`\n   - `get_status(execution_id)`\n   - `get_result(execution_id)`\n4. Add error handling and retry logic\n5. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_execution_client.py`\n\n---\n\n### Task 1.2: Output Formatter Module\n**Objective**: Create output formatting utilities\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create `cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`\n2. Implement formatters for:\n   - JSON output\n   - Table output\n   - Status color coding\n3. Add support for custom formatting options\n4. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_formatter.py`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Invoke Command\n\n### Task 2.1: Input Parser\n**Objective**: Parse various input formats\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create input parsing utilities\n2. Support JSON string, key-value pairs, file input\n3. Validate input against basic schema\n4. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/internal/input_parser.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_input_parser.py`\n\n---\n\n### Task 2.2: Invoke Command Implementation\n**Objective**: Implement the invoke command\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create `cmd/cli/invoke.py`\n2. Implement argument parsing\n3. Integrate with ExecutionClient\n4. Implement sync and async modes\n5. Add output formatting\n6. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/invoke.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_invoke_command.py`\n- `tests/integration/test_invoke_workflow.py`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Status Command\n\n### Task 3.1: Status Command Implementation\n**Objective**: Implement the status command\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create `cmd/cli/status.py`\n2. Implement argument parsing\n3. Implement polling logic with configurable interval\n4. Add watch mode support\n5. Integrate with ExecutionClient\n6. Write unit tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `cmd/cli/status.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_status_command.py`\n- `tests/integration/test_status_workflow.py`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Integration\n\n### Task 4.1: CLI Registration\n**Objective**: Register commands with main CLI\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Update `cmd/cli/main.py`\n2. Add invoke subcommand\n3. Add status subcommand\n4. Verify command hierarchy\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Updated `cmd/cli/main.py`\n\n---\n\n### Task 4.2: End-to-End Testing\n**Objective**: Validate complete workflows\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Create E2E test suite\n2. Test invoke → status workflow\n3. Test error scenarios\n4. Test edge cases\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- `tests/e2e/test_invoke_status.py`\n- Test report\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Documentation\n\n### Task 5.1: Command Documentation\n**Objective**: Document usage and examples\n\n**Steps**:\n1. Write invoke command documentation\n2. Write status command documentation\n3. Add examples to help text\n4. Update README if needed\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Updated documentation\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Prerequisites\n- AR-018 or later (CLI framework stable)\n- Backend execution API available\n\n### Optional Enhancements\n- Real-time status updates via WebSocket (future)\n- Log streaming for running executions (future)\n\n## Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Estimated Days |\n|-------|-------|----------------|\n| Phase 1 | 1.1, 1.2 | 1 |\n| Phase 2 | 2.1, 2.2 | 1.5 |\n| Phase 3 | 3.1 | 0.5 |\n| Phase 4 | 4.1, 4.2 | 0.5 |\n| Phase 5 | 5.1 | 0.5 |\n| **Total** | | **3** |\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/plan.md","time":{"start":1775891625448,"end":1775891625471}}}}
