{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891625841,"sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","part":{"id":"prt_d7b61725e001jR6KkNUrLVU7Bk","messageID":"msg_d7b614c31001nsVBe1DJLU9Tdz","sessionID":"ses_2849f24e1ffeeewZ5S6mmQ6lGS","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-023\ntitle: CLI invoke/status 命令\nmodule: cmd/cli\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令\n# Module: cmd/cli\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: cli-command\n  description: |\n    Implement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI.\n    The `invoke` command triggers an agent execution with specified inputs.\n    The `status` command queries the execution status of a running or completed agent invocation.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - cmd/cli/invoke command implementation\n    - cmd/cli/status command implementation\n    - Execution request submission\n    - Execution status polling/querying\n    - Input parameter handling\n    - Output formatting (JSON, table, etc.)\n    - Error handling for execution failures\n    - Real-time status updates (optional for status command)\n  out:\n    - Agent runtime implementation\n    - Backend execution engine\n    - WebSocket/real-time streaming implementation\n    - Log aggregation system\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - Invoke command submits execution request to backend\n  - Supports passing input parameters as JSON or CLI arguments\n  - Returns execution ID immediately for async tracking\n  - Status command queries execution by ID\n  - Shows execution state (pending, running, completed, failed)\n  - Displays execution results when complete\n  - Supports polling interval configuration\n  - Handles timeout scenarios gracefully\n  - Returns proper exit codes\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - https://docs.python.org/3/library/argparse.html\n  - https://docs.python.org/3/library/json.html\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: M\n  story_points: 5\n  days: 3\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-022/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775891625436,"end":1775891625837}}}}
